SIMPLE: snub
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snub
<hw>Snub</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>snuiven</ets> to snort, to pant, G. <ets>schnauben</ets>, MHG.
<ets>sn⟦umac⟧ben</ets>, Prov. G. <ets>schnupfen</ets>, to sob, and E.
<ets>snuff</ets>, v.t.]</ety> <def>To sob with convulsions.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snub</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Snub
<hw>Snub</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Snubbed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Snubbing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Icel. <ets>ssnubba</ets> to
snub, chide, Sw. <ets>snubba</ets>, Icel. <ets>snubb⟦omac⟧ttr</ets>
snubbed, nipped, and E. <ets>snib</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To clip
or break off the end of; to check or stunt the growth of; to
nop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To check, stop, or rebuke, with a tart, sarcastic
reply or remark; to reprimand; to check.</def> <rj><au>J.
Foster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To treat with contempt or neglect, as a forward or
pretentious person; to slight designedly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To snub a cable</b></col> <it>or</it> <col><b>To
snub a rope</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>to check it
suddenly in running out.</cd> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snub</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Snub
<hw>Snub</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A knot; a protuberance; a
song.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[A club] with ragged <qex>snubs</qex> and knotty grain.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A check or rebuke; an intended slight.</def>
<rj><qau>J. Foster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Snub nose</b></col>, <cd>a short or flat nose.</cd> --
<mcol><col><b>Snub post</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Snubbing
post</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a post on a dock or shore,
around which a rope is thrown to check the motion of a
vessel.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snub-nosed</ent>⟦br⟧
